It may seem a bit potty - but this beautifully carved giant teapot is actually someone's dining room.

The astonishing structure forms part of a tree house lived in and designed by elderly Chinese hermit Gu Yuezi, of Chen Village, Guangdong province.   

The 64-year-old root carving artist has decided to become a recluse and live in the jungle near the city of Foshan, in the south of the country.

