He came up with the crazy idea after tiring of the hustle and bustle of city life and the former landscape designer has retired from all commercial-related activities.

His wacky establishment consists of a giant tea pot, a bird nest and a root statue - all erected by himself.

The whole structure is around ten square metres in diameter, underpinned by six trees and is equipped with a hall, a bedroom, a bathroom and a kitchen.

And with the floor made of bamboo, the quirky home can bear the weight of up to 20 people.

Mr Yuezi says the tea pot is used as a dining hall where he can entertain guests - while the bird nest is his dedicated studio for painting, calligraphy and carving.

